# ============================================================
# TimeMachine Backup - Server List
# ============================================================
# List of servers to back up, one per line.
# Format: <hostname> [OPTIONS]
#
# Options:
#   --files-only      Only backup files (skip database dump)
#   --db-only         Only backup databases (skip file sync)
#   --no-rotate       Skip backup rotation for this host
#   --priority N      Backup priority (1=highest, default=10)
#                     Servers with lower numbers run first.
#   --db-interval Xh  Extra DB-only backups every X hours
#                     (e.g. --db-interval 4h = 6 DB backups/day)
#
# Lines starting with # are comments.
# Blank lines are ignored.
#
# Servers are processed in priority order (lowest number first).
# The number of parallel jobs is controlled by TM_PARALLEL_JOBS
# in your .env configuration.
# ============================================================

# === Critical Production Servers (high priority) ===
# web1.example.com --priority 1
# db1.example.com --priority 1 --db-interval 4h
# app1.example.com --priority 2

# === Standard Servers (default priority 10) ===
# staging1.example.com
# dev1.example.com --priority 20

# === File-Only Servers (no database) ===
# relay1.example.com --files-only
# monitor1.example.com --files-only

# === Database-Only Servers (frequent DB backups) ===
# db-replica1.example.com --db-only --db-interval 2h --priority 1

# === DNS / Infrastructure ===
# ns1.example.com --files-only --priority 5
# ns2.example.com --files-only --priority 5
